  "text": "Salvage RP was performed and evaluated in patients with recurrent PCa after radiotherapy. Five years after sRP, 48% of the patients were free from biochemical recurrence (BCR) and, 10 years after the surgery, 37% were still BCR-free [CITATION_1] .",
